  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nCSI allows 0.x drivers only in the deprecated kubelet plugin dir.\r\nCSI allows 1.x drivers only in the new kubelet plugin dir.\r\n\r\nIf a driver implements both 0.x and 1.x (which is unlikely since the side car containers do not support this), kubelet requires the driver live in new kubelet plugin dir.\r\n\r\nSo CSI drivers that implement both 0.x and 1.x if they want a seamless transition between k8s 1.12 to 1.13 would need to deploy in both old and new dir.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n@liggitt argues that this is adding churn for CSI authors. He recommends allowing any driver that implements 0.x (even if it implements 1.x) to use either new or old (not just new).\r\n\r\n/milestone v1.13\r\n\r\nIf release team approves, PR is small and I can get prepare it pretty quickly.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n<!-- DO NOT EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->\r\n/kind bug",
